# Testing Policy

## Runner and layout

- **Runner:** Vitest (`npm run test` fast suite; `npm run test:slow` for tiktoken-heavy tests; `npm run test:all` for both). SSOT config: `@vitest.config.ts`, `@vitest.slow.config.ts`, how-to: `@.cursor/skills/testing/SKILL.md`.
- **File naming:** co-located `foo.test.ts` next to `foo.ts` (not `.spec.ts`).
- **Imports:** NodeNext — use `.js` extensions in test imports (same as production code).
- **No ad-hoc scripts:** do not add `scripts/test-*.ts`; put tests under `src/**/*.test.ts`.

## Test environment

**Current state:** no dedicated test environment (no isolated Supabase / Redis / BullMQ stack for CI).

**Default:** mock external boundaries for **all** test types — unit, integration, component, system/E2E. Tests must not require prod/staging `.env` credentials.

| Term in Arcane | Means |
|----------------|-------|
| Integration test | **Mocked integration** — supertest + `vi.mock` services, not live DB |
| Component test | Testing Library + mocked `fetch` / API client, not real backend |
| System / E2E test | Playwright + `page.route()` / API mocks, not full stack against staging |

**Quarter scope:**

- **Q3 2026 (current):** unit tests + mocked smoke (waves 0–2 in coverage plan). No live DB, Redis, worker, or Playwright gates.
- **Q4 2026+ (future):** expanded mocked integration (supertest, Testing Library, Playwright) — still mock-first until test env exists.
- **Future prerequisite:** dedicated test environment — only then revisit live integration; not planned for Q3.

See `@docs/05-plans/testing-baseline.md` and `.cursor/plans/coverage_improvement_plan_926cfce7.plan.md`.

## When to write tests

| Situation | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| Bug fix in pure logic (`engine/`, `shared/`, utils) | Add regression test in co-located `*.test.ts` |
| New SSOT module in `engine/` or `shared/` | Unit test covering main branches |
| Zod/query helpers in `src/api/` | Test normalization and schema parsing |
| Preact page layout / styling | Skip unit tests unless extracting pure helpers |
| Route handler with Supabase calls | **Q3:** extract + unit test helpers; mocked middleware (`req`/`res`/`next`). **Q4+:** mocked supertest routes (still no live DB until test env) |
| Live LLM / OpenAI API | **Never** — mock provider (see `@src/engine/providers/openai.completejson.test.ts`) |
| Live Supabase / Redis / BullMQ | **Never** until dedicated test environment exists |

## Test types in Arcane

| Type | Q3 approach | Q4+ (still mock-first) | Blocked until test env |
|------|-------------|------------------------|------------------------|
| Unit | pure logic, co-located | same | — |
| Mocked integration | `validateRoute` middleware, mocked `supabaseDatabase` | supertest + service mocks | — |
| Component | pure hook helpers only | Testing Library + mocked `fetch` | live DOM + real API |
| System/E2E | — | Playwright + API mocks / route interception | live full stack |

## Layer boundaries

| Layer | Allowed in tests | Forbidden |
|-------|------------------|-----------|
| `src/engine/**` | Pure pipeline, glossary, prompts, mocked LLM | HTTP, Supabase, `req.log` |
| `src/shared/**` | Pure utilities, business rules | DB, Redis |
| `src/api/**` | `validateRoute` helpers, Zod; mocked middleware (Q3) | Full Express app without mocks |
| `src/client/**` | URL builders, pure hook helpers | Full component render without Testing Library + mocks (Q4+) |

## Gates

- Before **push:** `npm run lint:all` and `npm run test` (enforced via `.husky/pre-push` after setup).
- Before **commit:** pre-commit runs lint-staged only (fast).
- **Coverage:** monitor with `npm run test:coverage`; `coverage.include` is `src/**/*.ts` (excludes `src/client/**` until Q4+); no CI thresholds yet; `coverage/` is gitignored.

## Coverage policy

- Track trend, not absolute %.
- Prioritize `engine/` and `shared/` pure modules over UI pages.
- Do not add coverage thresholds until baseline is documented in `@docs/05-plans/testing-baseline.md`.

## Documentation workflow

When changing runner, gates, or test conventions:

1. Update this rule (`testing.mdc`) and `@.cursor/skills/testing/SKILL.md`.
2. Mirror to `@docs/_canonical/rules/testing.mdc`.
3. Update `@AGENTS.md` commands table if scripts change.

## Agent routing

- Test infrastructure, migration, coverage baseline → **Testing** utility agent (`@.cursor/agents/testing/AGENT.md`).
- Feature code + tests → domain agent (Engine/API/Backend/UI) + **verifier** runs `lint:all` + `test`.
